<p local-id=3D"63f58fa73a99"><strong>Indicative Size: M</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"cf7b24ca268f">Rationale: Known platform (Artifactory is alre=
ady approved and in use). However, migration from multiple current stores, =
pipeline repointing across multiple teams, RBAC design, and repository stru=
cture. Design constitute meaningful multi-component work requiring security=
 and operational involvement.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"a8cb5cf2b2e4">
<h2 local-id=3D"447002133e16" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-Dependency&amp;EngagementA=
ssessment">Dependency &amp; Engagement Assessment</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"33be8567a1c9" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-InternalTeamsLikelyRequire=
d">Internal Teams Likely Required</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"17c983a6e5a4">
<li local-id=3D"6b7dbceb2946">
<p local-id=3D"57ac926a296b">[x] <strong>Security Architecture</strong> =E2=
=80=94 RBAC design, Xray/scanning integration, access policy sign-off</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"e423ce739cd2">
<p local-id=3D"270e02082da9">[ ] <strong>Networks</strong> =E2=80=94 Not an=
ticipated unless Artifactory instance connectivity requires changes</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"66ceb5c935ad">
<p local-id=3D"206cbfa2b94d">[x] <strong>Application Teams</strong> =E2=80=
=94 All teams with pipelines consuming or publishing to current file shares=
 / FSx / S3 will need to repoint</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5e49e83b80c5">
<p local-id=3D"e7d0935bdb56">[ ] <strong>Product / Commercial</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Not required at this stage</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"abd856a27482">
<p local-id=3D"fef4f5b3a164">[x] <strong>Procurement</strong> =E2=80=94 =E2=
=9A=A0=EF=B8=8F Validate whether the UK Artifactory instance has sufficient=
 licence capacity/storage for expanded scope; additional licencing may be r=
equired</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"79f4d812a110" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-ExternalorNon-TeamDependen=
cies">External or Non-Team Dependencies</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"7b5ab1104fe0">
<li local-id=3D"f1b11127bd4d">
<p local-id=3D"694243a00a3e">[x] <strong>Vendor / SaaS provider</strong> =
=E2=80=94 JFrog (Artifactory vendor) =E2=80=94 confirm UK instance spec, st=
orage limits, and Xray licence tier</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3d9bf717604c">
<p local-id=3D"b188234d9983">[ ] <strong>Regulator / External Audit</strong=
> =E2=80=94 Not directly, although ESRO mandate implies internal governance=
 body sign-off</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"dc229e75093f"><strong>Dependency Risk: Medium</strong></p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"4becb4c651d6">
<p local-id=3D"5ff5131ca205">The number of pipelines and teams currently us=
ing the fragmented storage locations is unknown. Until this is mapped, the =
scope of integration work carries uncertainty. This is the primary risk to =
delivery estimate accuracy.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"9d34e52a0ed2">
<h2 local-id=3D"38892caf2fda" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-Risk&amp;Uncertainty(Quali=
tative)">Risk &amp; Uncertainty (Qualitative)</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"f0f15b76f21f" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-KeyAssumptions">Key Assump=
tions</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"ddc78ea1e1b9">
<li local-id=3D"182ea0da2ebe">
<p local-id=3D"f8f5fc86025d">The UK Artifactory instance already exists and=
 is operational =E2=80=94 this demand is about migration and consolidation,=
 not a new Artifactory deployment</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"caf1d39cecbc">
<p local-id=3D"4dc379b6c01d">ESRO mandate is confirmed and current (not sup=
erseded by a later directive)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b6a685ac81c6">
<p local-id=3D"c947eaf77bbe">Artifactory has or can be licensed to the requ=
ired storage and user capacity for full consolidation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ce0a0140942b">
<p local-id=3D"df126d1e6105">Current file shares, FSx, and S3 bucket usages=
 have not been fully catalogued =E2=80=94 a discovery exercise will be need=
ed</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"96e9e65e6ea8" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-KnownUnknowns">Known Unkno=
wns</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"9a6020cbd875">
<li local-id=3D"9d56b1488a70">
<p local-id=3D"35cac46c4ce6">Full inventory of current dependency storage l=
ocations, sizes, and consuming pipelines =E2=80=94 this is the critical unk=
nown</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1e3c7b14d697">
<p local-id=3D"42dfd3541fe6">Whether any dependencies stored in current loc=
ations are unique/legacy and not available via Artifactory remote repositor=
ies</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8164b45be9b2">
<p local-id=3D"5ab3eee7cf01">Whether the UK Artifactory instance is configu=
red for Xray scanning =E2=80=94 if not, this is scope that should be includ=
ed</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b6905483176a">
<p local-id=3D"20b48f8aeae9">Licencing position =E2=80=94 existing licences=
 may not cover expanded scope or storage requirements</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4a109f8c9c0a">
<p local-id=3D"75f9ac6bc6b0">Whether any teams have hardcoded dependency pa=
ths in pipelines (common toil risk)</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"c9ef4dd8702f" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-LikelyPainPoints">Likely P=
ain Points</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"82e7ce89df96">
<li local-id=3D"1bc7704e0225">
<p local-id=3D"bf174c9f1209">Pipeline repointing is often more widespread t=
han initially expected =E2=80=94 teams may have dependencies embedded in ma=
ny places (Terraform config, ADO YAML, bespoke scripts)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3b18480f631e">
<p local-id=3D"77c234eac86e">Legacy internal packages (e.g., EMIS Web insta=
llers) stored on file shares may require re-packaging or re-publishing to A=
rtifactory =E2=80=94 non-trivial for large installer binaries</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"25bfb973cf55">
<p local-id=3D"5233a4326ef8">Access control standardisation =E2=80=94 curre=
nt stores likely have inconsistent permission models; normalising to Artifa=
ctory RBAC will require engagement from multiple teams and may surface late=
nt access issues</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6476ee077338">
<p local-id=3D"8e2640da2ccd">Testing effort =E2=80=94 pipeline integrity mu=
st be validated after repointing to ensure no broken builds or missing depe=
ndencies</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"69c565f4dcf2">
