></p>
<hr local-id=3D"7d47787e1eff">
<h2 local-id=3D"ef1aee9c3539" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-Recommendation">Recommenda=
tion</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"6f1d3aadbd49" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-=E2=9C=85RecommendedDispos=
ition:Prioritise=E2=80=94ApprovewithConditions">=E2=9C=85 Recommended Dispo=
sition: <strong>Prioritise =E2=80=94 Approve with Conditions</strong></h3>
<p local-id=3D"e3f13476aac7">This demand is well-aligned with the approved =
technology roadmap (Artifactory is the Strategic IaC tooling platform). Dir=
ectly addresses a real and growing threat vector (software supply chain att=
acks), and is mandated by ESRO. The benefit-to-complexity ratio of 1.4 indi=
cates a strong return on the delivery investment.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3e635195d88e"><strong>Conditions for progression:</strong></=
p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"dfb7928a8a75">
<li local-id=3D"5d647ad1ef16">
<p local-id=3D"a1185db1a134"><strong>Discovery First</strong> =E2=80=94 Bef=
ore HLD work begins, a lightweight dependency mapping exercise must be comp=
leted. To catalogue all current storage locations (file shares, FSx, S3 buc=
kets) and identify all consuming pipelines and teams. This scopes the M-siz=
e accurately and prevents cost and timeline surprises.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e8e8f377fdfa">
<p local-id=3D"515317c0e962"><strong>Licencing Confirmed</strong> =E2=80=94=
 Procurement must confirm the UK Artifactory instance can support expanded =
scope within the current licence. Or identify the cost delta for upgrade. =
=E2=9A=A0=EF=B8=8F If licencing uplift exceeds =C2=A325,000 one-off or =C2=
=A350,000 annually. A formal cost approval gate is required.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"556f96319796">
<p local-id=3D"14433032cc9a"><strong>Xray Scanning Included in Scope</stron=
g> =E2=80=94 The supply chain security benefit of this demand is only fully=
 realised if Artifactory Xray is enabled for vulnerability scanning of depe=
ndencies. This should be confirmed in scope and not left as a follow-on.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"f68ebb56905a">
<p local-id=3D"a5782691e203"><strong>Security Architecture Engaged Early</s=
trong> =E2=80=94 RBAC design and access policy must involve Security Archit=
ecture before the LLD is completed.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"d181174e8ac2" id=3D"PLATENG-I-25-SuggestedNextSteps">Sugges=
ted Next Steps</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"f8526f83db3e" class=3D"conf=
luenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"95c6511da072">
<th data-local-id=3D"c5e3f648e686" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"4590b0986147">Action</p></th>
